casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellant, v. Kennedy, Appellee. (Two Cases.)

[Cite as State v. Kennedy (1992), 63 Ohio St.3d 353.]

(Nos. 91-691 and 91-692 Submitted February 25, 1992 Decided April 8, 1992.) John T. Smiley, Prosecuting Attorney, for appellant. G. Ian Crawford, for appellee Janet Kennedy, in case No. 91-691, and appellee Greg Kennedy, in case No. 91-692.

The causes are reversed on authority of State v. Eaton (1969), 19 Ohio St.2d 145, 48 O.O.2d 188, 249 N.E.2d 897, paragraph one of the syllabus, vacated on *354other grounds (1972), 408 U.S. 935, 92 S.Ct. 2857, 33 L.Ed.2d 750; and State v. Poindexter (1988), 36 Ohio St.3d 1, 5, 520 N.E.2d 568, 572.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Holmes, Douglas, Wright, H. Brown and Resnick, JJ., concur.
